(40, 4, 24, 2, 15, 26, 26, 'healed them', 'Healing and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing, with Matthew highlighting Jesus'' ability to heal various ailments and Exodus presenting God as the healer who protects from diseases. This connection highlights the continuity of divine healing authority from the Old Testament to the New Testament.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
